Executive Profile
Lisa   Gersh  Independent Director, Hasbro, Inc.AgeTotal Calculated CompensationThis person is connected to 2 Board Members in 2 different organizations across 9 different industries.See Board Relationships58$341,742
Background

		Ms. Lisa Gersh served as the Chief Executive Officer of Goop Inc. Limited (Goop.com) since October 2014. Ms. Gersh served as the President of Martha Stewart Living Omnimedia Inc. from June 2011 to February 7, 2013 and served as its Chief Executive Officer from July 2012 to February 7, 2013. Ms. Gersh served as the Chief Operating Officer of Martha Stewart Living Omnimedia Inc. since June 2011. She joined Martha Stewart Living Omnimedia, Inc on June 6, 2011 and was responsible ... for all aspects of MSLO's day-to-day operations. She also overseen Martha Stewart Living Omnimedia, Inc 's businesses, which include Publishing, Broadcasting and Merchandising. She served as Managing Director of The Weather Channel Interactive, Inc. She served as Managing Director of The Weather Company, LLC. Ms. Gersh served as the President of Strategic Initiatives of NBCUniversal, Inc. since 2009. She served as President of Strategic Initiatives at NBCUniversal Media, LLC. She served as President of Strategic Initiatives at NBC News. Ms. Hall played an instrumental role in NBC Universal’s multi-billion dollar acquisition of The Weather Channel Companies and served as its Interim Chief Executive Officer since 2009. While at NBC Universal, Ms. Hall pioneered the creation of the company’s groundbreaking Education Nation platform. Ms. Hall joined NBC Universal in 2007 after acquired Oxygen Media. She co-founded Oxygen Media, LLC in 1988 and served as its President and Chief Operating Officer since July 2004. Ms. Hall led the day-to-day operations of Oxygen Media, LLC and served as the principal engineer of Oxygen's foundation partnerships with Carsey-Werner LLC and Harpo Productions, Inc. She was also responsible for Oxygen Media, LLC's financing and major MSO agreements and in 2004 led Oxygen to its first year of positive cash flow. Ms. Hall was principally responsible for the sale of Oxygen to NBC Universal. She served as the Interim Chief Executive Officer of The Weather Channel Interactive Inc. from September 2008 to July 2009. She played a major role in securing distribution for the women-oriented network, which is in 52 million homes. In addition, she engineered Oxygen's foundation partnerships including Carsey-Werner-Mandabach, Harpo, Vulcan and financing. She founded the New York law firm Friedman Kaplan & Seiler LLP, where she served as a founding partner from 1986 to 1998. She started her legal career at Debevoise and Plimpton. Ms. Gersh has over 15 years of experience in creating strong corporate partnerships, negotiating financing and other strategic relationships. She has been a Director of comScore, Inc. since June 9, 2017. She has been an Independent Director of Hasbro, Inc. since July 1, 2010. She served as a Director of Martha Stewart Living Omnimedia Inc. from July 2011 to February 7, 2013. She served as Director of XO Group Inc. (alternate name: The Knot, Inc.) from June 6, 2005 to June 29, 2010. Ms. Gersh holds a B.A. in Political Science and Economics from the State University of New York Binghamton in 1980 and a J.D. from Rutgers Law School in 1983 and admitted to the New York State Bar Association in 1984.Read Full Background




