                                                    Hasbro posts smallest sales beat in 1-1/2 years, shares drop
                                                


                                                    Reuters – 
                                                    6:54 AM ET 07/24/2017
                                                


* Q2 EPS 53 cents vs. est. of 46 cents. * Q2 revenue $972.5 mln vs. est. of $972.4 mln. * Hasbro's (HAS) shares slump as much as 9.2 pct. By Gayathree Ganesan. Toymaker Hasbro Inc's quarterly sales scraped past analysts' estimates, marking its smallest beat in more than one and a half years, propped up by demand for its Transformers and Nerf toys in the United States.

















                                                    Hasbro earnings beat forecasts, revenue falls short
                                                


                                                    MarketWatch – 
                                                    6:51 AM ET 07/24/2017
                                                


Shares of Hasbro Inc. (HAS) fell slightly in premarket trading Monday after the toy maker reported earnings. Hasbro's (HAS) adjusted second-quarter earnings per share came in at 53 cents from 41 cents a year ago. A survey of analysts polled by FactSet Research forecast EPS of 45 cents per share on revenue of $974.2 million.

















                                                    BRIEF-Hasbro Inc reports Q2 earnings per share $0.53
                                                


                                                    Reuters – 
                                                    6:43 AM ET 07/24/2017
                                                


Hasbro Inc (HAS). * Qtrly net revenues for international segment $426.6 million, up 6 percent. * Hasbro (HAS) reports revenue, operating profit and net earnings growth for second quarter 2017. * Q2 earnings per share $0.53. * Q2 revenue $972.5 million versus i/b/e/s view $972.4 million.













						                            
			                                Hasbro 2Q revenue $972.5 million vs. $878.9 million year ago
			                            


			                                MarketWatch – 
			                                6:37 AM ET 07/24/2017
			                            
















                                                    Hasbro's quarterly sales rise 10.6 pct
                                                


                                                    Reuters – 
                                                    6:36 AM ET 07/24/2017
                                                


Hasbro Inc (HAS), the No. 2 U.S. toymaker, reported a 10.6 percent rise in quarterly revenue, helped by demand for its Transformers and Nerf toys in the United States. Net income attributable to Hasbro (HAS) was $67.72 million, or 53 cents per share, in the second quarter ended July 2, compared with $52.11 million, or 41 cents per share, a year earlier.













						                            
