                                                    Hasbro Reports Revenue, Operating Profit and Net Earnings Growth for Second Quarter 2017
                                                


                                                    Business Wire – 
                                                    6:30 AM ET 07/24/2017
                                                


PAWTUCKET, R.I.---- Hasbro (HAS), Inc. today reported financial results for the second quarter 2017. Net earnings for the second quarter 2017 increased 30% to $67.7 million, or $0.53 per diluted share, compared to $52.1 million, or $0.41 per diluted share, in 2016. The Hasbro (HAS) team executed another very strong quarter across the Brand Blueprint. Our balance sheet and cash flows remain strong.

















