                                                    UnitedHealthcare Donates Hasbro's NERF ENERGY Game Kits to Boys & Girls Clubs of Central New Mexico to Encourage Physical Activity
                                                


                                                    Business Wire – 
                                                    3:37 PM ET 07/13/2017
                                                


UnitedHealthcare donated 150 NERF ENERGY Game Kits, a limited-release game that tracks physical activity and rewards kids for being active, to the Boys & Girls Clubs of Central New Mexico this morning. This Smart News Release features multimedia. Each kit includes a NERF ENERGY Game Band, a NERF PRO FOAM soccer ball and instructions to download the NERF ENERGY RUSH mobile game to get kids moving.

















                                                    Mattel seeks to replace veteran finance chief Kevin Farr-WSJ
                                                


                                                    Reuters – 
                                                    10:59 AM ET 07/13/2017
                                                


Toymaker Mattel Inc is looking to replace its chief financial officer, Kevin Farr, the Wall Street Journal reported on Thursday. The move to replace Farr, who has served as Mattel's (MAT) finance chief since 2000, comes amid efforts by Chief Executive Margo Georgiadis to shake up the toymaker's senior management, the Journal reported.












